caption: I had a wonderful experience! The staff was professional and super friendly. I loved the music and the atmosphere. The food was good overall. I had the grilled eggplant as starter and I LOVED it, perfect score! The braised pork was tasty but a bit too sweet for my taste. For dessert, I had the Panna cotta, it was good nothing mind blowing. In sum, I will definitely recommend this place.
Vintage swanky vibes, good food. Appetizers and main courses were delicious, not a huge fan of the deserts.
The restaurant is on the Chicago restaurant list. I like the price and the pork belly but I will try the fried chicken next time.
Outstanding food. We went for restaurant week 2021, and the options were interesting. The flavors were delightful and unique without being over-the-top. Service, ambiance, etc. were all great.
Great service and food with many International flavors and plenty of space.

Terrible food and service. We went here to celebrate my birthday. Got a variety of items and one after another it was horrible. The only thing palatable was the elote. The scallops were really spicy and overcooked, lambchops were tasteless, shrimp pancakes were dry. The dessert tasted like chalk. After spending 300$ I had food poisoning that night and haven’t recovered 2 days later. Not to mention the server was not very welcoming. We wanted more information about the food and wine but she kept talking about the price point. I think we can afford it since our bill was $300 and still tipped 20% because we felt bad that the restaurant business isn’t doing well as is due to the pandemic. I wouldn’t return here. What a disappointment.
Great cocktails and food accomodations. Atmosphere is relaxed but upscale. I highly recommend for a nice date night or business meal!
Great food and atmosphere 👍👍👍
Great food, nice atmosphere, trendy cocktails. A solid west loop joint

One of my new favorite spots in Chicago! Chef Andrew Zimmerman's restaurant absolutely lives up to the hype, and I was excited to see that Proxi had reopened for indoor dining. As big fans of global street food, my girlfriend and I struggled to order as every dish sounded incredibly appetizing.  You absolutely HAVE to get the tempura elotes - they're the most popular item and a menu staple for good reason. The muhamarra was my personal favorite - even as someone who does not love pomegranates, this dish was phenomenal.  The scallops and khanom krok were both good, I would recommend the latter if you are looking for something a bit heavier.  The two of us chose to split 4 small plates  and one dessert and left satiated but not stuffed. Service was attentive and the ambience was great. I would love to come back, and intend to visit its sister restaurant Sepia very soon!

We tried lots of different plates and most were very good. Ambience was perfect for a low key date night or a celebratory dinner with a smaller group of family/friends. The dessert, however, was the highlight. The chocolate custard stole the show. Cocktails are equally good and they have an extensive bourbon/scotch selection.  This place has Michelin star caliber.

Awesome food, awesome drinks! My only complaint is that the prices were slightly too high for the portion size on some items. For example, if you're going to charge more than 10 bucks for hummus, then give a little more than 4, quartered pita bread slices.  Minor gripe, but it was slightly annoying.
Amazing meals and service

I have been to Proxi four different times and it’s always consistent and fantastic! It’s the most beautiful restaurant inside and the food is so tasty! I love to try all the things on the menu but my go to is always the elotés!

Proxi had delicious food, it was four of us and we split everything. We got: Tempura elotes (great, sweet, hint of the Mexican elote version taste but different. Burrata (delicious and it came with nicely toasted bread) Aloo tikki chaat (Indian inspired dish - good) Red lentil hummus (very good, sweet taste, tastes like there is an Indian spice in it) Lamb chops (very delicious, looked medium rare cooked where I like more medium to medium well, but it was very well cooked through) Whole fish (de-boned, nicely prepared, my bf and friend loved it) Wagyu beef (one of my favorite dishes, delicious) Almond parfait (the best out of three dessert we got) Vietnamese ice cream sandwich (this has coffee ice cream and it was too bitter) Coconut panna cotta (light and delish)  Overall very nice restaurant, adheres to all guidelines for covid. Shareable tapas style plates. Great dinner, would definitely go again!

The food was delicious. We really enjoyed the tempura elotes and the steamed halibut collar. The desserts were delicious and not too sweet. They are taking all the appropriate safety precautions seriously. Our server was attentive and nor overbearing.
1st time visit and felt welcomed by Dierre the Host. Outstanding food and service by Naomi our server and bar staff. We love the food and will be back.
Great food and amazing atmosphere. Go here if you haven't been

I love coming here with my family. The food is amazing, the staff is kind, and the restaurant is beautiful. Furthermore, I was extremely impressed by the precautions they took because of COVID-19. Definitely a restaurant you have to see in Chicago.

With all the stellar reviews I was pretty excited to check Running Goose out, but my excitement was premature after having a very mediocre experience with the food. The restaurant is comprised of a small indoor dining area with a much larger outdoor seating area that can accommodate larger parties with reservations. Perfect for those days with nice weather.
Still as flavorful as before! This place always gives me an enjoyable dining experience!
Good food

We were recommended to go to Proxi after going to    Sepia first! Rebecca at Sepia highly recommended it and you can’t go wrong since it’s literally right next door!  The cocktails were phenomenal! So fresh and flavorful at the same time, bartender Jess is the best! The food!!! we tried three small plates—tempura elotes, Lamb manti, and baby octopus, trust me when I say you can’t go wrong.  Must try! You won’t be disappointed!!

I'm not sure how to describe the interior, it felt warm, and modern. I was also distracted by the different food coming out. I think they are true to their self description. We had 5 or 6 items from their menu. Fancy street food from around the world. I think they surprise at the taste level, and look forward to revisiting.
The tempura elotes and the burrata were stellar! Highly recommend this restaurant. The service was great and all the staff were very knowledgeable about the food. The atmosphere was great too!

The meal enjoyed at Proxi was outstanding!! Our server suggested 4-6 dishes for two of us and it ended up being perfect, although the pork shank was much larger than expected so we left very full. The flavor combinations in all of the dishes were so bold and complex and inventive!! The tempura elote was such a fun and delicious concept. The baby octopus was charred and crunchy and tasty. The broccoli salad and the yellowtail dish were highlights because they were bursting with flavor and were so unique. The pork shank was my least favorite because I am not the biggest fan of the flavor of anise/five spice, but overall it was still very well prepared. We had so much trouble narrowing down the menu because everything looked so good, but we chose well and will be back to try more items soon!!

We started with a cocktail at the bar; the bartender was super-friendly and gave great advice. The drinks were all delicious; the bar staff has created some fun drinks. We then took our seats in the dining room, which is a great space with slightly industrial feel. Our servers were relaxed and helpful. We shared several plates and were really impressed by the totality of the meal. Standout dishes included the mung bean dumplings, the mushroom and yuba noodles, and the crispy rice cakes. The wine list also had some cool options, and we enjoyed our selection.
Great cocktails
The service was exceptional. The drinks and food were awesome. The atmosphere was great (whomever did the music playlist for Valentine's Day...you did an incredible job). I highly recommend.
Excellent, diverse menu of small-ish plates.Good service, comfortable ambiance.  Good for conversation, but also hAndles large tables well.

My boyfriend surprised me with a Valentine dinner at Proxi. Overall must say it was an amazing experience. Besides the 30 minute wait for our table (he made reservations at 10pm and when we got there our table still wasn’t ready) we went to the bar area to get cocktails and to wait. Once we finally got to our table, everything from the seating area (we got a really great spot) to the service to the Valentine course meals was exquisite. The music was just right to have a great conversation. Service was exceptional, having each meal plate replaced right away after we finished with a course, water refilled right away and overall a good explanation of the meals when we weren’t sure what to get. The meals were out of this world, flavorful & unique! The menu was inspired with international options. Delicious, delicious, delicious! In addition, the dessert was so well chosen together that your taste buds were buzzing with smoothness and creaminess. Overall, recommend this restaurant to anyone that wants to take their significant other to a upscale place with amazing food & service.
Table was 30 min late, food was ok, service extremely slow.

It's the best I've had and would definitely order again. The pizza was probably the standout. We got the guanciale pizza. It was almost perfect.  The guanciale added enough salt content to the pizza without needing any extra from the capers. It was a little distracting, but I still enjoyed it overall.

Food and food was ok. Smaller portions and very high prices. The prices is why it lost two stars. Dinner for a double date will cost you into the 400's and you will not feel full. Trendy and hip for the cliche crowd.

Great food. I’m docking 2 stars because there’s no changing table in any of the six restrooms (despite plenty of room for them to fold down behind the door). Staff gave no solutions when asked, either; just apologized. It’s 2020. A lack of changing tables is just ignorant. We have a *very well-behaved* infant and changing her during our 2-hour, $200 meal was more challenging than it needed to be.

Tempura Elotes - Good and unique Seared Scallops - ok Stone Bass - ok Grilled Pork Secreto - favorite thing I tried New York Strip Steak - good but not worth $45 Grilled Wagyu Short Rib Kalbi - good but not that flavorful
The food is excellent, but the service can be spotty.
Great food! We went for NYE dinner and it was amazing. Service was amazing and I am going to visit again.
Great bar program to be paired with exceptional food!!
Excellent drinks, fun atmosphere and delicious food. Eat here.

(Translated by Google) First, the environment is very quiet and comfortable to my liking Secondly serving speed and service are probably wait a few minutes time soon Secondly, very good taste Special unexpectedly delicious Scallop Lamb and Sea Bass are amazing seafood dishes is a must In addition to Yellowtail Salad salty and sweet little line can be said to be perfect food can give a comprehensive 4-4.5 star to 5 stars  (Original) 首先环境很合我意 安静惬意 其次服务和上菜速度都很快 等待时间大概就几分钟 其次味道很不错 Special很出乎意料地好吃 Scallop Lamb 和 Sea Bass 都很惊艳 海鲜类的菜真是一绝 除了Yellowtail Salad过咸和甜品不大行以外 可以说很完美了 食物可以给个4-4.5星 综合给5星
Food was good, but not worth the price. Overall, I was underwhelmed.

My best friend and her husband who are naive Chicagoans have raved over this place. We joined them for dinner last night (on a Thursday). Our reservations were for 8PM and they told us that the people at the table were paying and we would be seated shortly. The restaurant was not crowded and there were many empty tables.  We went to the bar and had a drink. I had the take on the old fashioned and it was well balanced. The highlight was actually Keep it spicy which is a non alcoholic drink. The spice of the ginger is magical. We ended up waiting 20 minutes for our table.  We finally got to the table and started to look at the menu. Our friends gave us some recommendations, but our waiter did not say anything. He did not offer suggestions or tell us how large or small the portions were. For starters we had the cauliflower Indian special, the burrata, and the elote. These dishes were the highlight of the meal. The cauliflower was super crispy and the sauce was so rich and flavorful with a hint of spice. The elote was crispy with a creamy corn flavor in the middle. The burrata was creamy and I liked the addition of the squash. It needed acid to cut the fat. The bread was perfectly grilled and seasoned.  We ended up ordering more drinks after the first courses and we waited around 15 minutes to get them. Our waiter never refilled our water glasses.  For the rest of the meal, we had the mussels and coal oysters. The mussels were great. The broth was bold and flavorful and I like the addition of the saltines of the sausage. The oysters should not happen. They were torched, but had no flavor. The oysters were cooked and were very one note. It ended up being a weird texture.  We also had the lamb chops, which were cooked perfectly. The raita could have been seasoned more. The pork shank fell off the bone, but the sauce was too sweet. It had a great heat, but finished sweet. We could have done away with the pork. We had no idea how large the portions were and it ended up being a lot of food for us and our friends ordered more.  There were some dishes that were more successful than others. For the price of the meal, the service did not match it. I wouldn’t come back again because nothing really popped, the food or the service.

Menu looks interesting, but most of the dishes we tried failed to deliver overall.  Favorite dishes were the yuba noodle salad and the wagyu short rib.  Tempura elotes, mung bean dumplings, baby octopus, pork shank, “tandoori” (burnt) lamb chops, lamb kabob, duck all missed somewhere (flavor, texture, execution, portion size)  Great wine and dessert though. The coffee flavored chocolate custard was perfect.

It’s not an accident this restaurant is on every Chicago list. It is a must visit. Came solo after a long day on a business trip and had a truly excellent experience from top to bottom. Huge comfortable table at the bar, kind and prompt service and fantastic ambience.  And then there’s the food. The tempura elotes were good. The yellowtail and pomelo salad was, without exaggeration, divine. Each bite delivered rich and complex flavors and the portion was extremely generous. Closed strong with the Thai Mussels, which were also fantastic. Another very generous portion, with a nice side of sticky rice so that none of the sauce went to waste.  What satisfies me the most was the shockingly reasonable prices of everything, including cocktails. For one of the best restaurants in the city, it might also be one of the best values for the variety and power of the flavors you’re getting in each dish. My only regret is I didn’t bring more people with me so I could try more.
Great food and great staff

Nice atmosphere and very good service, but the food was just mediocre for this price level.  Dinner for two with one decent scotch and two average glasses of wine was $200 with tip.  For that price, food needs to top tier.

This place was delicious. We went for brunch on Sunday, walked in hostess was very friendly. Our server was fantastic, making sure to take time to walk us through the menu and select the right dish. Our food was outstanding. Atmosphere was cool and comfortable.  Prices were affordable. We will be back.
Great cocktail. Atmosphere was good. I ordered the dessert and its was delicious. Great place. Staff were nice.
Incredible, some of the best food I've ever had
Great food variety, wonderful service and atmosphere

Coming back to Chicago for dinner and theatre, decided to try a new spot. Proxi is reviews were good and, after having travelled through Spain, we loved the idea of an eclectic mix of small plates. The tempura elote was awesome! All the flavors of Mexican street corn but in a pillow of air! Best dish was the mussels and Thai sausage in a spicy broth with basil and lemongrass. We had several other tastings and the only dish that somewhat disappointed was the jerk chicken as the meat was a bit over cooked, but overall a delightful evening with a taste for everyone! Staff was very attentive and helpful with the menu- a nice pre theatre dine or just getting together with friends.

Coming back to Chicago for dinner and theatre, decided to try a new spot. Proxi is reviews were good and, after having travelled through Spain, we loved the idea of an eclectic mix of small plates. The tempura elote was awesome! All the flavors of Mexican street corn but in a pillow of air! Best dish was the mussels and Thai sausage in a spicy broth with basil and lemongrass. We had several other tastings and the only dish that somewhat disappointed was the jerk chicken as the meat was a bit over cooked, but overall a delightful evening with a taste for everyone! Staff was very attentive and helpful with the menu- a nice pre theatre dine or just getting together with friends.

Service was spot on, Jordan was fantastic, very attentive and personable.  Atmosphere was high energy, slightly louder than I would prefer for a "date night" but manageable for a casual outing, however, still maintained a luxury feel.  My companion and I went big and tried almost everything and it ALL was lovely, the elotes live up to the hype, the scallops, were no doubt, the best I have ever had!  The lamb chops second only to my own, truly a Chicago dining highlight, top of my list of places to impress with.
Absolutely delightful. There is a little bit for everyone, and the dishes are inventive enough that there are no repeat flavors.
Excellent food!! Great for large groups The food was flavorful and had good variety .
Great food and services is awesome from front to back

We stopped by because it was near our hotel and it blew us away. The food is absolutely fantastic.  There were two of us and we picked four different plates and that was enough for us, though we could have gotten one or two more and been full. We chose the red lentil hummus, carrot salad, scallops, and the black pepper pork. Everything was incredible.  The only drawback to this place, for me, was the seating; there isn't much room between tables and it feels very cramped. It was difficult to get to the seat on the inside (the booth seat).  Other than the seating, which I didn't feel was important enough to drop a star, this place is amazing and I will definitely go back.
Great ambience, a bit pricey for their food portions.

Mushroom and yuba noodle salad was excellent; the waiter was knowledgeable about the menu and made good suggestions to help compose a balanced flavor profile.  I appreciated the variety of small plates and the quality of the kitchen's execution on the dishes.
We had a great server and a great time.
Delicious and wonderful service.
Excellent place for dinner. The small plate flavors are exquisite and the variety well balanced so there's something for everyone. Definitely coming back!
Wow!

Chic, modern and cozy ambiance. Noise level was a bit higher than I would have preferred even with the elevated ceiling but the mood was on point. In terms of the menu, the cocktails were good and the country ham? which was the special was really good. I would say that the octopus and the scallops were superb as well. However the grilled pork Secreto was a little bit too salty and strong in taste. Would recommend for a date night or a gathering with friends.

Proxi’s menu is the perfect result from a fusion between Indian and Mexican cuisines! This might sound odd at first, but the outcome is great! We came for brunch and decided to order lots of food to share. The elote tempura was crispy and warm. The chickpea curry was very tasty, with the right amount of spiciness. Lastly, the grilled cornbread with ham, poblanos and poached eggs left us begging for more!
One of my favourites :-)

Delicious food & incredible cocktails! My advice is to sit down at the bar, try a few different cocktails & order a handful of small dishes off of the menu. You’ll want to try everything! Staff is super friendly & the atmosphere is perfect for after work drinks, date night, anniversaries, birthdays, etc.
Love the small plates and cool vibe
Delicious food, lovely ambiance and great selection of wines by the glass!
Awesome
Good is great , though we felt like in a factory  , because of r estorant atmosphere - how hostess and waiters work

The global street food tapas are highly flavorful and delicious.  Sat near the open kitchen and drooled over every item that came out.  Very popular.  Make reservations many days ahead.  On the high side, but worth it!
Dude seriously some excellent food absolutely no complaints

Small plates, perfect for sharing. We were able to 'create' a meal that leaned on Asian influences and flavors, but expanded into other delicious cultures. Service was attentive and warm. Our meal began at the bar with a couple of delicious cocktails. From there we proceeded to the kitchen counter (a product of a late reservation, but an awesome vantage point!) for dining. Our servers helped explain the menu, but being able to observe the food being created helped us make the best decisions, lol.

Coming back to Chicago for dinner and theatre, decided to try a new spot. Proxi is reviews were good and, after having travelled through Spain, we loved the idea of an eclectic mix of small plates. The tempura elote was awesome! All the flavors of Mexican street corn but in a pillow of air! Best dish was the mussels and Thai sausage in a spicy broth with basil and lemongrass. We had several other tastings and the only dish that somewhat disappointed was the jerk chicken as the meat was a bit over cooked, but overall a delightful evening with a taste for everyone!Staff was very attentive and helpful with the menu- a nice pre theatre dine or just getting together with friends.
Fantastic array of food. Dishes are thoughtfully prepared to give a great tasteful experience.

Good food. I actually enjoyed the corn fritters and carrots the most! Had a nice variety of Asian inspired dishes like Kobe beef and fish. Enjoyed the atmosphere the most with service not far behind. Will be back.

Proxi is a Michelin star restaurant I visited in Chicago. My party of three ordered the recommended 2 or three dishes per person which included the whole fish(A delicatable white fish) the scallops, a fried mushroom dish, the steak, the pork shank and a round of custom made house cocktails. The meal for three was around $300 which to be honest being from LA I thought was extremely reasonable especially since my party ordered 4 cocktails which locally would usually add about $100 dollars to the tab. Not being from Chicago I might be understating the obvious but parking was attrocious and the Valet while extremely nice took me 20 minutes to track down.  Service was exceptional our waiter and support staff were on top of there game. Again I blame this on our lack of local knowledge but we arrived dressed for a Michelin resteraunt and were surprised to find local attire drofted towards the casual. The food was excellent all the way around and while our waiter was extremely accommodating he slightly over reccomended on dishes. Having said that the menu layout was divine with larger sized dishes being at the bottom of the menu and smaller at the top. Most of the "savory" plates listed on the far right of the menu like the whole fish and the steak are legitimately large enough portions to be considered a main course. Overall the experience was good with me reserving that final star becuase my expectations for a Michelin star resteraunt here in LA is extraordinary and this didnt wuite hit that level. But then again neither did the prices as locally I would expect to pay 30 or 40% more.
Found this on a list of best places to eat in Chicago, it wasn’t wrong! I had the most amazing tempura and short beef rib!

Such great food! Clean, bright and knowledgeable about the menu. Atmosphere is really cool, loved that you can see into the kitchen. Also, they are family friendly and accommodating to the stroller and car seat!

This place was delicious. We went for brunch on Sunday, walked in hostess was very friendly. Our server was fantastic, making sure to take time to walk us through the menu and select the right dish. Our food was outstanding. Atmosphere was cool and comfortable.  Prices were affordable. We will be back.
Small plates - international exectuedd well, great variety, fun twist on traditional, excellent service.
Best drinks in Chicago and great food

Proxi was a delightful surprise! We found it on our hunt for drinks/early dinner to celebrate a birthday. Our server, Rania, made this a very special night. She recommended the most delicious flavorful dishes, and we were sure to note the chef's name and seek his next creations. Overall, we left very happy (having ordered dessert too!) and the experience definitely exceeded our expectation!

One of my favorite small-plate/tapas style restaurants in Chicago! I've been here for both brunch and dinner and can attest to the quality of food and service here.  Brunch is Asian inspired, and I've tried their Vietnamese iced coffee, corn elotes, pandan French toast, and catfish banh mi. As a fan of sweet and creamy treats, the coffee and French toast are must-gets!  Dinner is definitely on the fancier side and perfect for a special night out.  Tip: definitely make a reservation for this place. They are accommodating to large groups, but the restaurant is always popular and packed.

We went for drinks on Saturday night. The cocktails were interesting, delicious and made with care. They were a bit sweet for my taste, although to be fair I didn't ask for less sweet drinks (I normally do). We were thinking of ordering dessert but ended up not having to order dessert because the drinks were sweet and delicious enough to count as dessert for us.  The interior of the bar/restaurant was very fashionable and visually interesting. We chose to sit in the middle of the restaurant where there is a section enclosed with curtains. We were seated in posh MCM chairs which were very comfortable and probably very expensive.  Service was friendly, professional and prompt. The bar was pleasantly busy, but we still had our choice of where to sit.

The good: two exceptional dishes- smoked pumpkin and then the mushrooms and soba 10/10 crazy good. The bad: the staff seem indifferent. Not friendly at all and they drop the food on your table like it's their recyclables. The acoustics are aweful with loud music. The space is too big. Feels like you are in some kind of chain restaurant.
Great food and high end cocktails.  Had a blueberry lemon cocktail that was perfect for the summer.
Amazing food and crazy good atmosphere

I was actually quite surprised about how much I liked this place. I wouldn't put it on the same level as some of the other similarly priced restaurants in the neighborhood, like Girl and the Goat. But my meal was absolutely fantastic.  The restaurant specializes in street food, the focus is on latin and asian cuisine. Everything is small plates and shareable.  First, the place just oozes style. I need to figure out what spotify playlist they're using, because I could not stop vibing to the music. It's not loud music by any stretch, but it's just the right volume for you to hear it and enjoy it without being obtrusive. And the interior is just very well decorated. It's weird to say, but I felt cool by just being there.  Second, the service was very good. Our server was attentive, knowledgeable, and gave strong recommendations.  Third, the food was really really good. Like I said, it's small plates, and they aren't cheap. If you're drinking, you should expect to spend close to $100 for a meal for two. But if you're looking for a cool and interesting place to have a great meal for a date night... I definitely recommend Proxi.
Fantastic drink selection
Wow fabulous food but bring a credit card with a high limit.  The wine will take a big chunk of your credit limit.
Great cocktails and dinner
Outstanding service. Some good food that has influence from all over the world. Some stand out dishes for our table were the corn fritters, the Korean rib eye, and the deserts.
Really good cocktails, the food is awesome as well

Delicious fresh flavors & interesting menu. The Kimchee beef short rib & curry stone bass were exceptional. Vietnamese crepe followed close behind. Never thought pumpkin tasted so good; hummus style preparation infused with smoked paprika & dried pomegranate seeds....

Wonderful! Great atmosphere, helpful service, and delicious food! The whitefish pomelo salad and the kalbi short rib were the stand-out dishes, with the scallops a close second. Drinks are creative and great. Dessert didn't live up to the food standards but was good. Highly recommend it.
Good please good service good food Good

Really fun and varied menu. I was a little worried that the concept wouldn't work but the level of execution, across the board, was very good. From the simple shaved zucchini to the duck leg curry, the flavors were great and everything worked well. Save room for dessert.
Great Food and service. Loved the duck.
Meh, it was ok. Nothing special. Food was kind of bland and definitely overpriced.

Great meal. It's all small plates to share.we loved the beet salad, wagyu short ribs and smoked oysters. Don't forget to get dessert. The flan and tres lesche cake were excellent. Service was good and the decor was very hip. Definitely would go back again.
Cool location

Proxi is a beautiful place and the service is good as well. But let me tell you its one of those upscale reataurants that definitely are well suited for satire. One can give and arm and a leg for a minimal meal. If you wanna impress a date and have appetizers go here. Other than that its all just a satirical experience
Really good food and amazing cocktails. Their late night smokey pumpkin is da bomb 🤤. Really good for a date night! We will definitely come back for their dinner and lunch menu.

This restaurant has many strengths. It offers creative and tasty culinary takes on International street food. Standouts include the Thai sausage and grilled oysters. It also boasts a large, interesting, space at once sociable and intimate. Wait staff is low key and efficient. Inventive cocktails. Nicely plated. Overall, a great dining experience.
Nice food good service
Outstanding!!!

Walked in at 7:48 for our 7:45 reservation and were seated immediately . This was my first time. I chose a nice glass of moscato and let my daughter, who had dined here before, order. It was beyond amazing. The tastes, the flavors, the textures, the freshness were five star all the way. There is nothing like it. The smoked pumpkin and the mushroom tuba noodle salad were especially delicious. The shrimp and bass curry was over the top good. I chose a blackberry pistachio dessert at the end and there are no earthly words to say how good and interesting it was. I will be back!

We had a reservation and waited 30 minutes to be seated. That said, the experience was made up for with the best service by Adam. He went above and beyond for everything despite a busy Saturday night. We requested a specific specialty cocktail which he was more than happy to accommodate. His recommendations of his favorite menu items were so on point! I'll be returning.
Interesting take on different cuisines. Good service
One of my favorite dishes is roasted baby potato with grilled half young chicken. It's a perfect combination.
Go see Chris at the bar.  Awesome bartender and loves to talk food and drinks.  Well worth your time to sit there with him.

Proxi is the coolest venue in the city! Andrew Zimmerman is amazingly talented & handsome. The combination of this cool, inviting vibe created by owner Emmanuel Nony and Chef Andrew Zimmerman along with all the staff make it a "first" on our list of places to dine in Chicago!
First of all our server Matt was the BOMB!!! VERY personable. Our food was very tasty for brunch and my Mother's Day was enjoyable.

Went in a larger group with 8 people. We made reservations ahead, and were able to get a private room which was really lovely for conversation. This restaurant is very beautiful. Given we were a large group, there was an option of a tasting menu. We went ahead with this and were not disappointed. The pumpkin dip is a *must*. There is a great selection of gin + tonics ! everything was delicious and service was timely. What more could one ask for?

Solid array of different flavors & dishes, from veggie heavy dishes to seafood & meat options. I personally enjoyed the pork secreto & thai sausage dishes. They also have an awesome mocktail & cocktail list.

Going back and forth on my opinions of this place. The food was decently good, though I don't know that it was five stars worthy given the other restaurants in Chicago. I found the menu and plates confusing for a table of six. Our waitor recommended the number of plates to order and a few plates that were popular.  Many of them were difficult to share, such as an entire fish or crepe. It ended up being a very messy experience trying them out.  Service was just ok. Plates did not come out with utensils so we ended up having to scoop things out with already used utensils. Curry is definitely not something to get into other plates! Took quite some to get it check after dessert.
We went to this new place for a business dinner.  Small dishes to share with options for everyone. The food was delicious and staff are very friendly. It was a bit too cold inside.
Excellent service and phenomenal food

Overall, we enjoyed the food and experience and would go back.  We had a 7:45pm reservation and arrived early. We had a drink in the bar area and were seated at 7:50pm. The waiter was very helpful and provided good recommendations. Generally the service was good although did get slightly less attentive toward the end of the evening.  We started with a couple cocktails that we enjoyed, and then my husband switched to wine and I ordered one of their more unique gin and tonics. I didn't love it and wouldn't order one again.  For food we largely went with some of the recommendations. For two of us we ordered 7 dishes to share and one dessert. That felt like the right amount. We enjoyed the roasted broccoli, smoked pumpkin, and short rib dishes in particular. The burrata was okay (wouldn't order again) and I didn't love the lamb kabob. The flan dessert was also good even though I don't love pineapple.  Overall a good choice for food and a lively atmosphere.
Excellent brunch.

Great food and amazing craft cocktails. Global cuisine that enthralls and transports in both small plate format and entree size. Sophisticated atmosphere and nice crowd to go with the food. Quickly becoming our once a week go-to dinner place.
The menu was fabulous ... Wonderful ingredients and very tasty. Service was exceptional, and I absolutely will return
Fabulous small plates. Great environment. Go.
Wide variety of small plates! Great solo or in a group!
So good, every dish was unique and had flavors from various parts of the world. Even the dessert had unique takes on various typical desserts, really loved this place. The drinks are great too!
they brought out little plate with a corm and a sauce and it was really good thabk u
Nice food but pretty crowded
Great brunch spot! Their take on Congee was really good
Food is great. Drinks are fun. Ice cubes are playful. Go here and sit at the counter so you can watch the chefs!
Great atmosphere and service from the lads behind the bar.
Went in for lunch with frnds. Good food. Def recommended
Great space, beautiful setup (take note of the arched ceiling architecture), drinks were fantastic. Old fashioned and, particularly, the Hendricks (pictured) were top notch.
Delicious, surprising food and stellar drinks.
Wonderful pineapple flan!
Tasty food. Tried a lot and everything was well seasoned.
Fun atmosphere and unique food
Don't forget to order the tempura ellote
Impeccable decor, drinks, and food. The best addition to Chicago’s food scene in recent times.
This place has really great duck dumplings. I would highly recommend them.
Great food for sharing and amazing desserts

The food are all very good. Everything was small plate and for sharing.  The top 2 for me were the Yellowtail Tartare and Vietnamese crêpe. The sesame leaves was a perfect contrast to the sweetness of yellowtail. The most unimpressive was the duck dumpling, it didn't taste anything like duck. We ordered the egg tart as dessert, because it was the most out of the ordinary. It was really good with matcha and jam. You only get 3 quarters of the tarte though. We joked that because there was only 3 of us.  We took their suggestion ordering 3 plates for each person, so we got 9 plus dessert. It was not enough for the 2 with bigger appetite and a lot for the small eater. So I'd think most men would wanna order more than we did.  Friendly and attentive staffs. The decors are very simple, modern and minimalistic, it has a cold and sleek feeling. Actually it felt like walking in high end men clothing store. There were mostly businessmen there too.
We really enjoyed this brunch! Awesome food like always!  Love this place!
Amazing service
right by the Metra! amazing time coming in from Glencoe. get the zucchini app!!!

Another good entry from Andrew Zimmerman, with a globally focused menu, interesting cocktails, and a beautiful interior. On the whole, the food is worth the price, the vegetable and seafood sections especially. Caution should be exercised on any "Asian" offerings, as these seem to get less thoughtfulness than other items (dry rice isn't acceptable at a restaurant of this caliber).

What an experience!  Beautiful decor, wonderful staff, a great night out. Everything was delicious.  The tempura elote was a surprise twist on a favorite, the duck dumpling was wonderfully seasoned, the mussels were an unexpected front runner.  Yet, the crepes were probably my favorite...sweet, savory, a little spicy.  I don’t often do dessert but the kulfi and chocolate custard were so light and rich, respectively, my mouth still waters.  You have to leave room for dessert!
Fun, creative and delicious. Very attentive service.
Dank little eats. Don't be the one paying and it's going to be an amazing time every time

Innovative brunch menu AND delicious! I was absolutely delighted with my congee bowl, the soft boiled egg was perfect and the dish bursting with flavor. The ambience is light, airy and sleek. Music seemed loud but at least they were playing a variety of good music. We'll return.
Proxi had an exciting atmosphere with very good food.
Incredible food and pretty good cocktails. But unfortunately, pretty over priced.

Surprisingly spacious, Proxi is a dream come true. With a menu inspired by street food from around the world, it was perfect for a large group with varying tastes. We got multiple plates of everything for sharing and no one left hungry. Drinks were also phenomenal. And everything was reasonably priced! (Except for maybe the steak but that was also entirely worth it.)
Outstanding small plates restaurant with a global theme!  Jennifer, the wine director, aces the pairings!
Great atmosphere. Party of  two, ate at the bar. Great drink mixes and small plates.
All of the vegitarian dishes wowed us
Perfect poached eggs and the best grilled sourdough bread! Delicious and fabulous service!
Delicious food, great ambience and service.
Everything tasted wonderful. Flavors were volume and well balanced. They also make a pretty good old fashioned with ice cubes clear as glass.
Good food, good service, creative apps.

Beautiful spot on a bustling corner. Large open windows and seating with open patio doors. This picture shows the cocktails  "Don't Chouette It", "Scofflaw", and "Drippin' In Finesse". Great food and drinks!!

Amazing brunch and great overall experience. The service was really nice - even from the point of the hostesses being so welcoming when we walked in. The food - wow the food! The menu is impressively creative with combined flavors from across the globe. The tempura elote lives up to the hype - melts in your mouth. The exec chef is also really impressive so to enjoy his menu at such reasonable prices is a great opportunity! Can’t wait to check out the dinner menu.

Some really clever fusion of Southeast Asian influences with western hemisphere dishes brings complexity and excitement to recognizable favorites. Coffee game is strong, everything was a hit. The tempura elotes and shrimp toast were standouts.
Sublime food
One of my favorite restaurant bars to have a drink and bite at in West Loop.
Great decor, Good food, and great service. The elotes are amazing.

I actually appreciated this restaurant, the food is incredible, and also the bathrooms were ok. It was a little cold indoors, really was not totally cool. The waiter is excellent too. I will most definitely think about returning again if I get the chance. Me and my good friend got the works and we were not disappointed. My one recommendation is to keep the cool exterior. See you all again.!

Came to town as a visitor on a business trip accompanied by my sister. We came to Proxi because of the convenience of location to our hotel. But, what we now have is a NEW Favorite Restaurant!!  The atmosphere is kind of jazzy and laid back especially if you dine in the lounge area. But the food and customer service are what make this place phenomenal! The manager, Valerie, is just amazing...and our server, Steve, was awesome! I would say this is not a family or kid-friendly restaurant as the setup and menu are more on the exotic side. I can't wait to bring my husband here to try it. The overall experience is like no other.

Very busy place with upscale dining.  We enjoyed our unique food choices.  The only reason I did not give it a 5 was because the seating want comfortable and after sitting for several hours the circulation in my legs was cut off and I couldn't walk for a bit.  If we would have been in a different type of table I don't think this would be a problem.
Chic Asian fusion ! Great cocktails and food is eccentric and delicious.
Great, sat at the bar.  The muscles are fantastic.
Food is outstanding, especially the smoked pumpkin and the peppered pork. The raspberry dessert is really good, so save room.
Fantastic food and service.
Excellent cocktails and a great atmosphere
Some of the best food I’ve had

Food is reeeeally good. Tried two small plates plus a dessert and got surprised and delighted by each of them. Flavors are balanced and make it for a unique experience. I'll definitely come back to taste more.  One thing to note though. Google maps classifies this as a $$ restaurant, but I think it fits more the $$$ category as you might need at least two small plates to be satisfied. But don't get me wrong, it is definitely worth it.
We were told street food inspired dishes, and I want to find those streets! Enjoyed wonderful sampling experience with my party. Some of the best cuts if meat I've had in ages.
Indonesian Pork jerky was excellent as was the shrimp crepes.  Service was excellent.
The food is incredible. Perfectly portioned and the cocktails go down smooth. Worth every penny.
Blew our minds. They treated us incredibly and the vibe was awesome

Very very good. It’s a tapas place that takes you on a journey with their plates.  I almost wanted a new plate for each tapa because they are so masterfully created that you feel like each one deserves it’s own spotlight. Delightful meal, worth savoring in the contemporary modern setting. Put your preferences aside and order anything on the menu, trust me.

Came here for a date night with my hubby. Proxi was on my radar because it was on the up and coming list of a food list I read (I forgot which publication). We decided on a whim to go and there no reservations available. However they told us they have a bar casual seating area that is first come first serve and that it’s usually not too bad. We decided to take our chances and go. When we got there, we said we were walk ins and they told us to go ahead and find a place to sit. We found a table almost immediately. The food is phenomenal. They’re tapas style, small portions meant to share. I still dream of that tempura elotes. Their drinks are SO delicious. I normally don’t get anything but the cocktail I got that night with lychee was outstanding. A good dinner experience I’ve had in a while.
The food was awesome. I'd recommend trying the pumpkin, mushroom salad/noodles, and the young chicken. It's expensive but delicious!!

Great food, atmosphere and cocktails. Menu changes so don't fall in love with anything because it will be gone. Steps from Olgivie Train station so it's the perfect spot for commuters grabbing drinks after work.

Came in for a few small plates and drinks. The Tempura Elotes and Bhel Puri we're some of the best appetizers I've had in a long time. Also had the Shaved Zuccini which was great as well. Will definitely be back.
My fav place in chi!!

Ate here with a bunch a friends. A nice big space at the east end of Randolph away from the craziness. A more formal but still casual location for delicious small bites. We had a variety of dishes including the duck dumplings and Thai wrap which were great. The two highlights were probably the grilled octopus and whole grilled fish. The weakest dish was likely the beef curry which should have been fall apart tender but was instead very hard and firm. A little disappointed with that one. Service was very good though and a great selection of wine and cocktails. Glad I tried this place out.

One of the most beautiful restaurant spaces we’ve been to in Chicago. Tons of variety and some unique dishes you probably won’t find elsewhere. Standout dish was the baby octopus and corn fritters. Need a reso to get a table.
Good, casual dinning
Great drinks and food
Mussels are amazing!
Lots of different flavors that somehow work together. Interesting evening.
Great spot. The Vietnamese crepe is a must have. The pork lettuce wraps a close second. Go with the custard for dessert.

Hearty dishes, artfully prepared with purpose. All the flavors, textures, and colors you hope for without the pretentious stuffy atmosphere of high end restaurants. The tasting menu was diverse,  delicious and showcased a lot of techniques that speak volumes about the staff working there. We're will be coming back.
Best food ever

Went for happy hour on a weekday after work. Got a couple drinks, shared the baby octopus and sweet potato salad. Food was delicious, service was fast, nice, and knowledgeable, and the atmosphere was very lively, fun, and cool.
One of my favorite places. If you like gin, this is your place. If you like fish this is your place. Get the cobia.
One of the shining stars in Chicago dining. Food is excellent,  flavorful, great textures,  great service

Beautiful restaurant design with a very upbeat feel. The menu is tapas/small plates style with a need to order 6-7 plates for 4 people then share. The food comes out in a timely manner, the flavors are out of this world and makes you wish you had one more bite of everything. The desserts are a favorite between here and sister restaurant Sepia. The cocktail program is phenomenal from champagne ice cubes to corn infused tequila with chili salt.
Really nice space.  Fantastic cocktails.  Beer prices were WAY off!  10 bucks for an Anti-Hero?  WHAT?!  The Bartenders were stellar.  Especially Nick.
Over hyped

Everything about this place is awesome! The food is more than 5 stars,  the drinks are awesome, the atmosphere is perfect even in the bar, the music the service is awesome and the management is on point. I’m coming back again and again!!
Upscale but ordinary small plate Randolph St. Eatery.  Slick interior, eclectic servers, staff & mediocre food.  NYC attempt resto fails miserably.
The asparagus were amazing and great drinks!
Proxi is great. Love the decor, food, and service. Eager to come back again soon.

Excellent place. Creative, small plates for sharing. Every dish had an ingredient I was not familiar with,  but it was all delicious. Atmosphere is lively but not so loud that we had to spend the evening shouting. Would definitely recommend.

A large reataurants with a nice modern decor. All dishes are for sharing and combine oriental flavours with local produce. Great black pork to be wrapped in lettuce leaves with a tasty dark sauce. Nice dumplings and other well done dishes. Small wine list with some good bottles.

OMG another restaurant that is very delicious loved everything from the small plates to the main plates to the dessert wine and drinks are purely delicious and satisfying don't believe me find out for yourself five stars automatically
I loved it. Amazing service, great location and authentic Italian food. High Level! Love this magic Place! Highly recommended!! Good job guys.
The food was impeccable, as were the cocktails. However what blew me away was the friendly staff and amazing service! Definitely worth checking out.
Great experience, we were a party of two and ordered 5 dishes. The burata was amazing.
Upscale, formal, great for business drinks or dinners. Food portions are reasonable and delicious.
Food and drink are always excellent here.
This place is beautiful.  A great and uncrowded  place for drinks. Very creative drink menu!

Great experience, came here for our anniversary and had an amazing time. Food was outstanding and our server Daniel was more than accommodating and knowledgeable. Lot of great places to come to the city and eat but I’m glad we came here. Cheers to the front of house and culinary teams, we’ll definitely be back!

Fabulous blend of flavors and foodie sensations on a hyper inventive, super original menu.  This is a dining experience that is closer to the west coast with the fusion of flavors, creativity in items, solid cocktail and ice program with a desert offering that’s not to be skipped. And the decor and ambiance drive you to linger long.  This is one of my Chicago current favorites.

Very interesting flavors. And in a Very good way. The wait staff (had Steve) understands the flavor profiles and drink pairings. Very talented bartenders and mixologists. Great use of the space for a relaxed and comfortable environment. Will definitely return!
incredible food. id say on par with girl and the goat. sharing small plates, it's excellent
Only had dessert and drinks but they were amazing. Staff was  great
Fantastic food with Asian and other ethnic influences. Well deserving of the accolades it has received in its first year!
Really just breath taking restaurant. The food is amazing.
Creative menu.  Attentive staff.  Excellent meal.  Worth a visit.
Fantastic cuisine and service!
Everything in the menu was good all the way to coffee and dessert. Ambiance was good too. Servers very knowledgable to whats on the menu. Great service. Will definitely come back
The food was good, the service however was  subpar. Had to ask for fresh plates after 4 course on the same ones. Server only came over when flagged down.
Excellent cocktails and every dish we ordered was delicious
Pricy for what it is. We ordered 6 dishes, and were wowed by only one. The mussels are not at all recommended. Very trendy atmosphere and great intertior.
